subject: Automobile Racing
organizations: National Assn of Stock Car Auto Racing
lead_paragraph: Nascar officials have told teams to remove an auxiliary air hose used to cool engines in an attempt to reduce speeds that in practice topped 200 miles per hour at Daytona International Speedway.
